</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[189,780,1998,2025]" box="[189,780,1998,2025]" pageId="18" pageNumber="93">Flowering from March to April, fruiting in March.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[189,587,264,291]" box="[189,587,264,291]" pageId="19" pageNumber="94">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,587,264,291]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="19" pageNumber="94" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,587,264,291]" pageId="19" pageNumber="94">Preliminary conservation status</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[189,734,311,338]" box="[189,734,311,338]" pageId="19" pageNumber="94">
Endangered, EN B2ab(iii) (
<bibRefCitation author="Lopes J. C. &amp; Vilela L. &amp; Johnson D. M." box="[511,721,311,337]" pageId="19" pageNumber="94" pagination="273 - 278" refId="ref22868" refString="Lopes J. C., Vilela L. &amp; Johnson D. M. 2021. Hornschuchia mellosilvae (Annonaceae) a new species endemic to the Brazilian Atlantic Forest. Phytotaxa 520: 273 - 278. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 520.3.6" type="journal article" year="2021">
Lopes 
<emphasis box="[592,651,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="94">et al.</emphasis>
2021
